The process is isothermal, so the ideal‑gas law gives  

\[
P_1V_1 = P_2V_2 \;\Longrightarrow\; 
P_2 = P_1\frac{V_1}{V_2}
\]

\[
P_2 = (1\times10^{5}\,\text{Pa})\frac{20\ \text{cm}^3}{5\ \text{cm}^3}
      = 1\times10^{5}\,\text{Pa}\times 4
      = 4\times10^{5}\,\text{Pa}
\]

**Resulting pressure:** **4 × 10⁵ Pa** (choice 2).
